cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CC 

This paper is about using the BERT model for commonsense reasoning, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of unsupervised models, which could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
